==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Butment
<hw>But"ment</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Abbreviation of
<er>Abutment</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A buttress
of an arch; the supporter, or that part which joins it to the upright
pier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Masonry)</fld> <def>The mass of stone or solid work
at the end of a bridge, by which the extreme arches are sustained, or by
which the end of a bridge without arches is supported.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Butment cheek</b></col> <fld>(Carp.)</fld>, <cd>the part
of a mortised timber surrounding the mortise, and against which the
shoulders of the tenon bear.</cd> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>But</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Butt</ent>⟦br⟧
